Subject: UPDATE RE: Genesis Mission Proposals -Note for PIs about PDG compliance review



An update from the Proposal Development Group:

A careful review of RFA Amendment 000001 reveals a number of small but important changes that were not mentioned in the list of changes on p. 1. 

 

Significant changes are:

·        Summary/ Abstract

o   Must specify “The project title, application stage (Phase I), the PI name and the PI’s institutional affiliation, and any coinvestigators and their institutional affiliations.”

·        DOE Title Page

o   Must specify “Application Stage: Phase I”

·        Appendix 2 Facilities and Other Resources

o   May be 1 page long

o   Includes the new instruction “Describe current computing allocations that will be used to support the proposed work, or the intent to apply for computing allocations. Computational resource estimates should also be provided in the Genesis Mission Phase I Application Template excel file attached to Field 12.” 

·        Appendix 6 Transparence of Foreign Connections

o   Reordered with changes, including:

·        The disclosure requirements are determined by the entity type. Even if the applicant is exempt, the subrecipients must provide these disclosures unless the subrecipient is also exempt 

·        Applicants, regardless of entity type, must provide complete responses for project team members that are not U.S. national laboratories, domestic government entities, or institutions of higher education. 

 

Also, the document that was referred to as “ Tables of focus area, senior/key personnel, partner institutions, and budget” is now referred to as ”Genesis Mission Phase I Application Template”.

 

Document “GM Phase I Application Guide - Argonne is Lead” has been modified to reflect the above changes.  

